review_blob: Pleasant, slightly fruity aroma. Beautiful straw color with a dense head. Flavor is mild malt, little hop, slight citrus with some spice. Fresh on the palate. I found it to be a pleasant balanced beer in the Belgian style. I might classify it as a Saison rather than a Strong Ale. I might compare it to Ommegang Hennepin Ale.
Mild spice in a tasty, yet thoroughly refreshing, context. This is one of the best beers I have ever tasted.
